		<a name="breakfast" id="breakfast"></a>
		<h2>French Toast</h2>
		<img src="Images/FrenchToast.jpg" alt="French Toast"/>
		<!---this image can be found at "http://rino-onir.blogspot.ie/2013/06/resep-french-toast-simpel-dan-enak.htmlhttp://rino-onir.blogspot.ie/2013/06/resep-french-toast-simpel-dan-enak.html"--->
		<h2>Ingredients</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>2 eggs</li>
		<li>1 cup of milk</li>
		<li>2-4 slices of bread</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Method</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>Mix eggs and milk well in a bowl.</li>
		<li>Dip the bread into the mixture.</li>
		<li>Heat oil in pan.</li>
		<li>Deep fry the bread</li>
		<li>Serve up!! (add any extras you fancy e.g banana,apple,custard.. etc.)</li>
		</ul>
		
		<a href="#breakfast">Breakfast</a> 
		<a href="#lunch">Lunch</a> <!--Links for each meal-->
		<a href="#dinner">Dinner</a> 
		
		<a name="lunch" id="lunch"></a>
		<h2>Tomato Soup</h2>
		<img src="Images/tomatosoup.jpg" alt="Tomato Soup"/>
		<!---this image can be found at "http://www.pasmama.lt/straipsnis/pomidoru-sriuba-su-ryziais-ir-darzovemis-440http://www.pasmama.lt/straipsnis/pomidoru-sriuba-su-ryziais-ir-darzovemis-440"--->
		<h2>Ingredients</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>400g can cherry tomatoes</li>
		<li>1 tablespoon of sugar</li>
		<li>100ml vegetable stock</li>
		<li>2 tablespoons of mascarpone</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Method</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>Put the tomatoes, sugar, stock and sauces into a medium pan with some salt and pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook for 5-10 mins.<li>
		<li>Stir in the mascarpone and blend to a smooth soup. Return to the pan and keep warm.</li>
		<li>Serve up!! (add any extras you fancy e.g bread,dippers.. etc.)</li>
		</ul>
		
		<a href="#breakfast">Breakfast</a> 
		<a href="#lunch">Lunch</a> <!--Links for each meal-->
		<a href="#dinner">Dinner</a> 
		
		<a name="dinner" id="dinner"></a>
		<h2>Chicken Pesto Pasta</h2>
		<img src="Images/chickenPasta.jpg" alt="Chicken Pesto Pasta"/>
		<!---this image can be found at "http://www.pinterest.com/sandracaz/http://www.pinterest.com/sandracaz/"--->
		
		<h2>Ingredients</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>500g of chicken breast or thigh</li>
		<li>About 20 cherry tomatoes</li>
		<li>1/4 cup of olive oil</li>
		<li>1 tablespoon of parmesan cheese</li>
		<li>2 and 1/2 tablespoons of minced garlic</li>
		<li>Any type of pasta</li>
		<li>Basil(optional)</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Method</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>Start boiling a pot of water for the pasta.<li>
		<li>Put the tomatoes, basil, oil, garlic, cheese in to a blender and blend up until smooth.</li>
		<li>Chop the chicken into pieces of your chosen size.</li>
		<li>Pre-heat a pan with olive oil for the chicken. Put the pasta in the pot.</li>
		<li>Cook the chicken in the pan of medium-high.</li>
		<li>Once the pasta and chicken are cooked, take both off the heat.</li>
		<li>Drain the pasta. Put the pasta back in the pot and keep off the heat.</li>
		<li> Put the chicken into the pot with the pasta and scoop about 1/4 cup of basil and tomato pesto into the pasta and chicken. Mix well.</li>
		<li>Serve up!! (add any extras you fancy e.g bacon bits, extra cheese... etc.)</li>
		</ul>
		
